race.comment: EXTRA ZERO (1) meets a moderate field and has been in the money three of his last four. Has a low gate and 3kg claim and is back in grade off his latest. Will race forward again and this is his race to lose. NOW SHOWING (2) draws awkwardly again but has been racing well without winning. Has placed 2/3 this course and distance and he should be in the finish. KALLAHTI (6) just missed here first-up over 1400m and had transferred from the Parnham yard. Has a cruel gate but he's got more upside than most of these and with the extra fitness has to be considered. SWISHGOBANGO (8) has switched stables on a 28-day return. Led and folded up here last time over 1925m, and coming back to a mile suits better. Has the rails gate, and the 3kg claim brings him into it.
